                    rr, cc = line[write_idx]
                    out[rr][cc] = 4
                    write_idx += 1

    # 1) Determine direction(s) from instruction panel(s)
    color_to_dir = find_panels_color_to_dir(grid)
    if not color_to_dir:
        return [row[:] for row in grid]

    # 2) Collect all 4s and assign each to a direction
    four_positions = [(r, c) for r in range(H) for c in range(W) if grid[r][c] == 4]
    if not four_positions:
        return [row[:] for row in grid]

    dir_groups = {}  # (dr,dc) -> list of positions
    unassigned = []

    # If only one direction exists, everything moves that way
    if len(color_to_dir) == 1:
        only_dir = next(iter(color_to_dir.values()))
        dir_groups.setdefault(only_dir, []).extend(four_positions)
    else:
        for pos in four_positions:
            best_dir = None
            best_dist = None
            for frame_color, (dr, dc) in color_to_dir.items():
                v, dist = first_nonzero_along(grid, pos, dr, dc)
                if v == frame_color:
                    if best_dist is None or dist < best_dist:
                        best_dist = dist
                        best_dir = (dr, dc)
            if best_dir is None:
                unassigned.append(pos)
            else:
                dir_groups.setdefault(best_dir, []).append(pos)

    # 3) Remove all 4s, then re-place moved ones after gravity
    out = [row[:] for row in grid]
    for r, c in four_positions:
        out[r][c] = 0

    for (dr, dc) in sorted(dir_groups.keys()):
        moving_set = set(dir_groups[(dr, dc)])
        apply_gravity_inplace(out, moving_set, dr, dc)

    # Put back any unassigned 4s
    for r, c in unassigned:
        out[r][c] = 4

    return out
